Package com.google.api.gax.grpc

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ChannelProvider
    Provides an interface to either build a gRPC ManagedChannel or provide a fixed ManagedChannel that will be used to make calls to a service.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CallableBenchmark  
    ChannelAsBackgroundResource
    ChannelAsBackgroundResource wraps a ManagedChannel so that it can be used as a BackgroundResource.
    FixedChannelProvider
    FixedChannelProvider is a ChannelProvider which always provides the same channel.
    GaxGrpcProperties
    Provides properties of the GAX-GRPC library.
    GrpcApiExceptionFactory
    A factory class that returns the corresponding type of exception class from the given status code.
    GrpcCallableFactory
    Class with utility methods to create instances of UnaryCallable with grpc-specific features.
    GrpcCallContext
    GrpcCallContext encapsulates context data used to make a grpc call.
    GrpcOperationFuture<ResponseT extends com.google.protobuf.Message,MetadataT extends com.google.protobuf.Message>
    An ApiFuture which tracks polling of a service, typically started by OperationCallable.futureCall(Object, ApiCallContext).
    GrpcStatusCode
    A failure code specific to a gRPC call.
    GrpcTransport
    A Transport for gRPC.
    GrpcTransport.Builder  
    GrpcTransportProvider
    A TransportProvider for grpc.
    GrpcTransportProvider.Builder  
    InstantiatingChannelProvider
    InstantiatingChannelProvider is a ChannelProvider which constructs a gRPC ManagedChannel with a number of configured inputs every time getChannel(...) is called.
    InstantiatingChannelProvider.Builder  
    OperationTimedPollAlgorithm
    Operation timed polling algorithm, which uses exponential backoff factor for determining when the next polling operation should be executed.
